{"id": "EUVD-2025-13979", "enisaUuid": "95fbc412-52ab-3417-bbf7-b19b3ba50ba1", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nusb: xhci: Fix invalid pointer dereference in Etron workaround\n\nThis check is performed before prepare_transfer() and prepare_ring(), so\nenqueue can already point at the final link TRB of a segment. And indeed\nit will, some 0.4% of times this code is called.\n\nThen enqueue + 1 is an invalid pointer. It will crash the kernel right\naway or load some junk which may look like a link TRB and cause the real\nlink TRB to be replaced with a NOOP. This wouldn't end well.\n\nUse a functionally equivalent test which doesn't dereference the pointer\nand always gives correct result.\n\nSomething has crashed my machine twice in recent days while playing with\nan Etron HC, and a control transfer stress test ran for confirmation has\njust crashed it again. The same test passes with this patch applied.", "datePublished": "2025-05-08T09:30:24", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-13T00:30:16", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-37813", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0624e29c595b05e7a0e6d1c368f0a05799928e30", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/142273a49f2c315eabdbdf5a71c15e479b75ca91", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1ea050da5562af9b930d17cbbe9632d30f5df43a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bce3055b08e303e28a8751f6073066f5c33a0744"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-37813", "GHSA-rc74-9j9p-c3xp"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "08bb9a72-e46a-3b91-bc8f-6a4e01c16f9a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.5"}, {"id": "26b8ba6e-0abd-35b0-8a0a-eb0ecfd02f95", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.13"}, {"id": "27eabe0b-b3e3-3fa1-89bd-3ed7dad0338c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.26"}, {"id": "38593fdb-4b5e-3492-a4f2-f170340284bf", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5e1c67abc9301d05130b7e2